div.p: SOOROOTOO Isle, a small island in the Eastern Seas, situated off the western coast of Borneo, and separated from the island of Carimatia by a narrow strait, through which a ship might run if compelled by necessity. Long. 108. 40. E. Lat. 1.45. S.
